Three men have been arrested in connection with the murders of women in Soweto. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng provincial police commissioner Deliwe de Lange has confirmed the arrest of three men in connection with the murders of women in Soweto.De Lange has set up a task team to investigate the recent murders of women in Soweto.The bodies of four women were found in various areas at the weekend.Added to this, 11 men have been charged with gang-raping a 22-year-old pregnant woman who was attacked while walking home from work on Monday.The police's Lungelo Dlamini they are trying to establish if the killings are linked. The detectives are still busy trying to locate other suspects because we believe the suspects were with other people when they killed these women. We are still trying to establish if the murders are linked. 